# ===== W2F .gitignore =====
# Track CODE + DOCS only. Large/regenerable binaries (weights, banks, datasets,
# samples) are built on demand (see README "Reproducing the paper") and are NOT
# committed.

# model weights / latents / feature banks
*.pt
*.pth
*.ckpt
*.npy
*.npz

# datasets, training outputs, run artifacts
/data/
/checkpoints/
/runs/
/samples/
/logs/
/remote_samples/

# generated images / figures (this repo intentionally omits the figure/montage
# ecosystem; any stray renders stay out of git too)
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.mp4
# ...except the self-contained slide deck's own assets, and the report's figures
!/presentation/assets/**
!/report/figs/**

# secrets — never commit credentials or host/key material
**/ssh_remote.txt
**/*askpass*
*.pem
*.key
.env

# local-only research history (kept on disk, not published)
/experiments/

# third-party Drifting repo if cloned locally (we link, not vendor)
/third_party/drifting/
/third_party/drifting_ref/

# python / tooling caches
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/
.DS_Store
*.tmp
